ART+THEATRE
 i read it somewhere, 'Being lazy is showing disrespect to the ones who believe in you.' 
 I've had my days where everything i did was worth questioning, but that followed with realising its not too bad either 
CONVENTIONAL/ UNCONVENTIONAL.... I've done both, only to realise its not about being an exception but just trusting your gut and knowing when to take a step and show up.
This mindset, the ability and the courage to try, fail and try again, to try, not just one kind but every other form of art, to see how things are actually done in a theatre play, how your perspective changes for everything you consume visually, the amount of work that goes behind making everything work, 
STILL IN AWE!
All worth it!
.
.
.
